18
00:03:11,954 --> 00:03:14,498
Long live our father, our tsar!

19
00:03:14,957 --> 00:03:16,959
Glory!

20
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,224
Damn!

21
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:19,105
Hey, what's the matter?
No electricity again!

22
00:04:19,397 --> 00:04:23,317
It's outrageous!
Timofeyev has burned the fuses again!

23
00:04:25,194 --> 00:04:28,489
- Comrade Timofeyev, when will it end?
- I'm finishing.

24
00:04:28,864 --> 00:04:31,534
When will be the end
of your experiments

25
00:04:31,826 --> 00:04:34,286
which leave our whole building
without electricity?

26
00:04:34,537 --> 00:04:35,913
There you go.

27
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:40,668
Ivan Vasilyevich, if you knew
what an important invention

28
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:43,379
I'm working on, you wouldn't have
said that.

29
00:04:43,754 --> 00:04:46,674
Experiments with electricity
should be done at your office,

30
00:04:46,924 --> 00:04:51,804
and at home electricity must be used
only for peaceful, domestic purposes!

31
00:04:52,304 --> 00:04:54,056
How many times did I tell you...

32
00:04:54,348 --> 00:04:58,185
I'm on leave, so I work at home.
And anyway, my experiments are safe.

33
00:04:58,436 --> 00:05:01,689
As the public representative,
I demand that you stop it!

34
00:05:02,064 --> 00:05:05,776
Today you've burned the fuses,
tomorrow you'll burn the house!

35
00:05:07,111 --> 00:05:08,446
STUPID

36
00:05:08,654 --> 00:05:11,073
And what is this?

37
00:05:11,323 --> 00:05:13,367
You see?
That's the result. Pah!

38
00:05:15,369 --> 00:05:19,081
I'll need to raise the voltage.

39
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:24,295
Dangerous! Of course, it's dangerous,
but, as they say, nothing ventured...

40
00:06:07,505 --> 00:06:13,135
Your only love
is not so easily found.

41
00:06:13,552 --> 00:06:19,141
Our planet's turning,
round and round.

42
00:06:19,850 --> 00:06:25,564
The planet's flying
in everyday beat.

43
00:06:25,981 --> 00:06:31,987
It's very hard
to fall in love on it.

44
00:06:34,323 --> 00:06:37,118
A winter blizzard is raging,

45
00:06:37,368 --> 00:06:40,079
And thunderstorms are blazing,

46
00:06:40,371 --> 00:06:45,835
And stars in the sky are racing,
and cities din in the rain.

47
00:06:46,544 --> 00:06:49,046
And people don't see each other,

48
00:06:49,422 --> 00:06:52,174
They just pass by each other,

49
00:06:52,758 --> 00:06:55,469
They always lose each other,

50
00:06:55,803 --> 00:06:59,890
Never to find again.

51
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:06,689
But there's somewhere
my only love,

52
00:07:07,648 --> 00:07:09,358
My unforgettable,

53
00:07:09,984 --> 00:07:13,028
My true big love.

54
00:07:13,529 --> 00:07:16,407
I look for it,

55
00:07:16,741 --> 00:07:19,160
But in everyday beat

56
00:07:19,869 --> 00:07:24,915
It's hard for us to meet.

57
00:07:28,627 --> 00:07:30,755
